<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>纽约时报 &amp;gt; 美国 &amp;gt; 政治</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/spotlight/on-politics</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 16:32:17 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>这些民主党人能让 2028 年选举出现好斗的中间派吗？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/02/us/politics/democrats-centrism-2028-election.html</link><description>温和的民主党倡导团体和智库“第三条道路”制定了一项规模庞大且耗资巨大的计划来塑造 2028 年总统竞选活动。</description><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 01:34:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/02/us/politics/democrats-centrism-2028-election.html</guid></item><item><title>读者对即将到来的德克萨斯州初选的评价</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/27/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</link><description>我们在该州的读者提供了了解当前政治世界中心的窗口。</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 23:42:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/27/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</guid></item><item><title>社交媒体如何塑造特朗普的国情咨文演讲</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/25/us/politics/trump-sotu-social-media-reactions.html</link><description>以下是社交媒体如何塑造您对国情咨文的印象。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:45:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/25/us/politics/trump-sotu-social-media-reactions.html</guid></item><item><title>关于特朗普国情咨文演讲的五个重大政治问题</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/23/us/politics/trump-speech-state-of-union-questions.html</link><description>关税、生活成本、移民：总统在重大问题上采取谨慎的路线。</description><pubDate>Mon, 23 Feb 2026 23:31:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/23/us/politics/trump-speech-state-of-union-questions.html</guid></item><item><title>人工智能将在 2026 年中期选举中亮相</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/20/us/politics/ai-midterms-elections.html</link><description>我们的科技专栏作家 Kevin Roose 解释了人工智能的潜在影响。</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Feb 2026 22:52:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/20/us/politics/ai-midterms-elections.html</guid></item><item><title>随着参议院初选提前投票开始，德克萨斯州选举季升温</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/18/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</link><description>两党的参议院初选正在紧锣密鼓地进行。</description><pubDate>Wed, 18 Feb 2026 23:06:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/18/us/politics/texas-elections-senate-primary.html</guid></item><item><title>为什么更多国会议员在 2026 年退休或不寻求连任？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/13/us/politics/congress-retirements-house-senate.html</link><description>对于许多参议员和众议院议员来说，这项工作已经不再是以前的样子了。</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Feb 2026 23:00:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/13/us/politics/congress-retirements-house-senate.html</guid></item><item><title>密歇根州参议院的民主党希望者争夺联邦支持</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/11/us/politics/democrats-michigan-senate-working-class-voters.html</link><description>民主党能赢回工人阶级选民吗？这些候选人正在努力。</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Feb 2026 23:09:50 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/11/us/politics/democrats-michigan-senate-working-class-voters.html</guid></item><item><title>共和党对 ICE 设施的部分抵制表明 MAGA 出现裂痕</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/09/us/politics/ice-detention-centers-republicans-trump.html</link><description>右翼分裂的迹象往往是由特朗普政府的行动加剧的。</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Feb 2026 23:04:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/09/us/politics/ice-detention-centers-republicans-trump.html</guid></item><item><title>马里兰州州长韦斯·摩尔谈 2028 年、民主党的问题和他最喜欢的蟹饼</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/06/us/politics/wes-moore-maryland.html</link><description>马里兰州州长讨论了特朗普、该国的分歧和他的锻炼习惯。</description><pubDate>Fri, 06 Feb 2026 23:33:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/06/us/politics/wes-moore-maryland.html</guid></item></channel></rss>